Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
getImportMode(25.10)                                      getImportMode(25.10)

Name
       getImportMode  -  Retrieves  the  current  settings  of all or specific
       setImportMode parameters

Syntax
       getImportMode

       [-help]

       [-keepEmptyModule]

       [-minDBUPerMicron]

       [-syncReLativePath]

       [-treatUndefinedCellAsBbox]

       [-quiet]

       Retrieves the current settings of all or specific setImportMode parame-
       ters. The setImportMode command controls how the software reads in  the
       Verilog netlist and other design files. For specified setImportMode pa-
       rameters,  getImportMode  displays the following information in the In-
       novus log file and at the console:

              * Parameter name

              * Current value

              * Type (Boolean, string, and so on)

              * Whether the current value was set by user

       If you do not specify a parameter, the  software  displays  information
       for all of the setImportMode parameters.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each getImportMode parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man getImportMode.

       <parameter_names>
              Displays information for the specified parameters. You can spec-
              ify one or more parameters.

              See setImportMode for descriptions of  the  parameters  you  can
              specify.

       -quiet Displays  the  current  settings for the specified parameters in
              Tcl list format only.

              If you specify -quiet without any parameters, the software  dis-
              plays  the  current  settings of all setImportMode parameters in
              Tcl list format.

Examples
              * The following command displays the  current  setting  for  the
                -keepEmptyModule parameter:

                getImportMode -keepEmptyModule

                The software displays the following information:

                -keepEmptyModule true # bool, default=true

                true

              * The  following  command  displays the current settings for all
                setImportMode parameters:

                getImportMode

                The software displays the following information:

                -minDBUPerMicron 0                # uint, default=0

                -syncRelativePath false           # bool, default=false

                -treatUndefinedCellAsBbox false   # bool, default=false

                {keepEmptyModule true} {minDBUPerMicron  0}  {syncRelativePath
                false} {treatUndefinedCellAsBbox false}

              * The  following  command  displays  the current setting for the
                -keepEmptyModule parameter in Tcl list format only:

                getImportMode -keepEmptyModule -quiet

                The software displays the following information:

                true

              * The following command displays the current  settings  for  all
                setImportMode parameters in Tcl list format only:

                getImportMode -quiet

                The software displays the following information:

                {keepEmptyModule  true}  {minDBUPerMicron 0} {syncRelativePath
                false} {treatUndefinedCellAsBbox false}

